#: core/analyzers/recommendations_registry.py:1335
msgid ""
"Arithmetic (* / + / -) on DECIMAL(38, x) columns implicitly widens the "
"result to DECIMAL(38, 18). At this aggregate scale, the widening inflates "
"per-row CPU and hash-table memory significantly. If the columns are integer-"
"valued in practice (counts, quantities), migrating to INT/BIGINT eliminates "
"the widening and enables faster Photon SIMD paths."
msgstr ""
"DECIMAL(38, x) カラムへの算術演算（* / + / -）は結果を暗黙に DECIMAL(38, 18) "
"に拡張します。この集計規模では行あたりの CPU とハッシュテーブルメモリを著しく膨張させます。実値が整数（件数、数量）なら INT/BIGINT "
"への移行で拡張を排除でき、より高速な Photon SIMD パスが有効になります。"

#: core/analyzers/recommendations_registry.py:1343
msgid ""
"Use DESCRIBE TABLE on the heaviest scanned table(s) to confirm DECIMAL "
"precision/scale. If a column is DECIMAL(38, 0) but holds integers, migrate "
"to INT/BIGINT. If wider precision is required, narrow it (e.g., DECIMAL(18, "
"2)) rather than retaining DECIMAL(38, *)."
msgstr ""
"最も重いスキャン対象テーブルに DESCRIBE TABLE を実行し DECIMAL precision/scale "
"を確認してください。DECIMAL(38, 0) でも整数値を保持している場合は INT/BIGINT に移行。広い精度が必要なら "
"DECIMAL(38, *) のままではなく DECIMAL(18, 2) などに狭めてください。"

